<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>{{ title }}</title>
<style>
body { font-family: Source Serif Pro, Georgia, serif; max-width: 900px; margin: 2em auto; padding: 0 1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #222; }
h1, h2, h3 { color: #0b3d66; }
h1 { border-bottom: 2px solid #0b3d66; padding-bottom: 0.3em; }
table { border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1em 0; width: 100%; }
th, td { border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 0.4em 0.8em; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
th { background: #f2f4f8; }
pre { background: #f6f8fa; padding: 0.6em; border-radius: 4px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 0.85em; }
img.figure { max-width: 100%; display: block; margin: 1em 0; }
.kq-block { background: #f6faff; border-left: 4px solid #0b3d66; padding: 0.5em 1em; margin: 1em 0; }
.custody { background: #fff8e1; border-left: 4px solid #d49b00; padding: 0.5em 1em; margin: 1em 0; }
.disclaimer { background: #fef1f1; border-left: 4px solid #a83232; padding: 0.6em 1em; margin: 1em 0; font-size: 0.92em; }
.lr-value { font-family: "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace; font-size: 1.2em; color: #0b3d66; }
.provenance { font-size: 0.85em; color: #666; margin-top: 3em; border-top: 1px solid #ccc; padding-top: 1em; }
.footnote { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>{{ title }}</h1>
<p>
<strong>Generated:</strong> {{ generated_at }} &middot;
<strong>tamga:</strong> {{ tamga_version }} &middot;
<strong>Report type:</strong> Forensic authorship-verification (LR framing)
</p>

{% if hypothesis_pair or questioned_description or known_description %}
<div class="kq-block">
<h2>Hypotheses under test</h2>
{% if hypothesis_pair %}<p><strong>Pair:</strong> {{ hypothesis_pair }}</p>{% endif %}
{% if questioned_description %}<p><strong>Questioned (Q) material:</strong> {{ questioned_description }}</p>{% endif %}
{% if known_description %}<p><strong>Known (K) material:</strong> {{ known_description }}</p>{% endif %}
</div>
{% endif %}

{% if acquisition_notes or custody_notes or source_hashes %}
<div class="custody">
<h2>Chain of custody</h2>
{% if acquisition_notes %}<p><strong>Acquisition:</strong> {{ acquisition_notes }}</p>{% endif %}
{% if custody_notes %}<p><strong>Notes:</strong> {{ custody_notes }}</p>{% endif %}
{% if source_hashes %}
<p><strong>Source-file hashes:</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>document id</th><th>original hash (SHA-256)</th></tr>
{% for doc_id, h in source_hashes.items() %}
<tr><td>{{ doc_id }}</td><td><code>{{ h }}</code></td></tr>
{% endfor %}
</table>
{% endif %}
</div>
{% endif %}

{% for result in results %}
<h2>{{ result.method_name }}</h2>

{% if result.lr_summary %}
<p><strong>Log<sub>10</sub>-LR:</strong> <span class="lr-value">{{ result.lr_summary.log_lr }}</span>
(Likelihood ratio: <span class="lr-value">{{ result.lr_summary.lr }}</span>)</p>
<p class="footnote">
Interpreted under the flat-prior convention: positive log<sub>10</sub>-LR favours the
same-author hypothesis; negative favours different-author. Magnitudes follow the six-band
verbal scale of Nordgaard et al. (2012), adopted in ENFSI (2015): 0–1 weak, 1–2 moderate,
2–3 moderately strong, 3–4 strong, 4–5 very strong, &gt;5 extremely strong.
</p>
{% endif %}

{% if result.figures %}
{% for figure in result.figures %}
<img class="figure" src="{{ figure }}" alt="{{ result.method_name }} figure">
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

{% if result.params %}
<h3>Parameters</h3>
<pre><code>{{ result.params }}</code></pre>
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}

<div class="disclaimer">
<h3>Evidentiary disclaimer</h3>
<p>
Output is intended to inform, not replace, expert forensic-linguistic judgement. Likelihood
ratios reported here are conditional on the specific known and questioned material, the
feature space chosen, and the calibration set used. Extrapolation to populations outside
the calibration conditions is not warranted. Reporting follows the framing recommended by
the European Network of Forensic Science Institutes (ENFSI 2015).
</p>
</div>

<div class="provenance">
<h3>Reproducibility provenance</h3>
<pre><code>{{ provenance }}</code></pre>
</div>
</body>
</html>
